cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper deals with Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) and their ability to model the distribution of natural images, which is a core topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the unsupervised learning of latent representations, which is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper proposes a new method for exploiting the internal capacity of GANs, which involves manipulating intermediate layers of the generator, which is a topic in neural networks (cs.NE) and multimedia (cs.MM).
